message: Tell me more about yourself and your background in software engineering.
I don't have much experience, but let's see where this interview goes
What motivated you to pursue a career in software engineering, especially considering your limited experience?
I just think it's really cool that you can make things out of nowhere. You know, you can just code things until work and it's just out of your pure creativity.
Can you share a project or an instance where you applied your creativity to code and develop something? What languages and technologies did you use?
I have not coded anything ever in my life so I don't really know how to answer this question

Given your interest in software engineering but absence of hands-on coding experience, have you taken any steps or are planning to take steps towards learning coding languages or software development practices?

Yes, I plan to do the Harvard CSFD course and I'm also planning to start by learning C and then learn Python JavaScript and then also you know understand how a computer works by doing a one-year course in a software, in a computer engineering college.

How do you plan to balance your learning between these structured courses and hands-on practical experience? Additionally, do you have a timeline or schedule set up for achieving these learning goals?
Not as of now, but hopefully within the next month or so I come up with a concrete plan.

Thank you for your participation and sharing your aspirations with us. It's clear that you have a strong interest in entering the software engineering field, and your future learning plans are commendable. I encourage you to proceed with your educational goals and perhaps consider engaging in small, personal projects as a practical application of your learning. Best of luck with your endeavors, and feel free to reach out in the future once you've gained some experience and are ready to pursue opportunities in software engineering.
